    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>tofu</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut the<strong> tofu</strong> into cubes</p><p>Add the <strong>tofu cubes </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and set aside to marinate</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-tofu-sweetcorn-and-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>chipotle paste </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong>\u00a0dried oregano </strong>and the<strong> </strong>juice of <strong>half</strong> your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon[s] </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong>,<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>\u00a0and mix to combine \u2013 this is your <strong>peri peri sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-tofu-sweetcorn-and-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>marinated tofu cubes</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, turning occasionally until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-tofu-sweetcorn-and-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the tofu is cooking, drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>red kidney beans</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>,<strong> </strong>pat it dry with kitchen paper, then remove 6 <span class=\"text-purple\">[8]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> <strong>outer leaves</strong> and set aside for later</p><p>Shred the<strong> inner core[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-tofu-sweetcorn-and-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>peri peri sauce</strong> to the pan with the tofu and cook over a high heat for 2-3 min turning a few times or until the sauce has reduced and the tofu is coated</p><p>Once done, remove from the pan and set aside for later (save the pan!) \u2013 this is your <strong>peri peri tofu</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-tofu-sweetcorn-and-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, in a separate small bowl combine the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>tangy</strong> <strong>lemon dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-tofu-sweetcorn-and-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> sliced shallot</strong>,<strong> drained sweetcorn </strong>and <strong>drained</strong> <strong>red kidney beans</strong> to the reserved pan with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika </strong>and cook for 2-3 min further or until the shallot has softened \u2013 this is your <strong>smoky sweetcorn & beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-tofu-sweetcorn-and-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Assemble the salad with the <strong>reserved lettuce</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> first, then add the <strong>smoky sweetcorn & beans</strong> and the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>peri peri tofu</strong> and drizzle over the <strong>tangy</strong> <strong>lemon dressing</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
